{"ID": 54059, "name": "Doggett v. United States", "href": "https://api.oyez.org/cases/1991/90-857", "view_count": 0, "docket_number": "90-857", "timeline": [{"event": "Argued", "dates": [686984400], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/52204"}, {"event": "Reargued", "dates": [698911200], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/51862"}, {"event": "Decided", "dates": [709362000], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/52203"}, {"event": "Granted", "dates": [667461600], "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_timeline/case_timeline/53611"}], "question": "<p>Should a mandatory requirement of actual prejudice be imposed in order for the accused to prevail on a claim that his right to a speedy trial has been violated?</p>\n<p>Has <i>Moore v. Arizona</i>, which holds that an affirmative demonstration of prejudice is not required, been reversed?</p>\n", "citation": {"volume": "505", "page": "647", "year": "1992", "href": "https://api.oyez.org/case_citation/case_citation/17988"}, "term": "1991", "description": null, "justia_url": "https://supreme.justia.com/cases/federal/us/505/647/"}